{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox serial killer |name=Akku Yadav |image= |caption= |birthname=Bharat Kalicharan |alias= |birth_date=1972 |birth_place=[[India]] |death_date={{Death date and age|2004|8|13|1972|df=y}} |death_place=[[Nagpur]], [[India]] |cause=[[Lynching]] |conviction= |sentence= |victims=3 |beginyear= |endyear= |country=[[India]] |states= |apprehended= }} '''Bharat Kalicharan''', alias '''Akku Yadav''' (1972 - 13 August 2004), was a 32-year-old rapist and murderer<ref>{{cite news | url= https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/nagpur/Trial-in-Akku-Yadav-murder-case-begins/articleshow/16920887.cms | title=Trial in Akku Yadav murder case begins | date=23 October 2012 | newspaper=The Times of India | accessdate=26 July 2018 }}</ref><ref name="guardian">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2005/sep/16/india.gender|title='Arrest us all': the 200 women who killed a rapist|first=Raekha|last=Prasad|date=16 September 2005|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=26 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html |title=In India, One Woman's Stand Says 'Enough' |first=Nicholas D. |last=Kristof |date=15 January 2006 |publisher= |via=NYTimes.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100209030954/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html |archivedate=2010-02-09 |df= }}</ref> in [[India]] who, on 13 August 2004, was [[Lynching|lynched]] by a mob of around 200 women from [[Kasturba Nagar]].<ref name="guardian" /> Yadav was stabbed over seventy times, and chili powder and stones were thrown in his face. One of his alleged victims also hacked off his penis. This lynching occurred in the [[Nagpur]] district court,<ref>http://www.humanrightsinitiative.org/publications/police/killing_justice_vigilantism_in_nagpur1.pdf</ref> on the marble floor of the courtroom. The women who killed him claimed that Yadav had been raping and abusing local women with impunity for over a decade, and that the local police had refused to help his victims or pursue charges as Yadav was allegedly bribing them. Yadav had also reportedly murdered at least three people and dumped their bodies on the railroad tracks. The lynching reportedly occurred when Yadav spotted a woman he had raped and called her a prostitute, enraging the crowd.
In 2012, Akku Yadav's nephew, Amar Yadav was stabbed to death following similar circumstances.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/nagpur/Teens-stab-to-death-Akku-Yadavs-nephew/articleshow/26925999.cms|title=Teens stab to death Akku Yadav's nephew - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref>
Five women were immediately arrested but released following demonstrations in the city. Every woman living in the local slum has claimed responsibility for the lynching. Usha Narayane, a local activist, was arrested and charged with murder, as were other women. In 2012, Narayane was released from custody.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://prezi.com/dbug9bmeyhkt/usha-narayane/|title=Usha Narayane|publisher=}}</ref> 21 other people, including six women, were also arrested and released due to lack of evidence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/india-news/in-lynching-of-alleged-rapist-in-nagpur-court-in-2004-all-accused-let-off-691479|title=In Lynching of Alleged Rapist in Nagpur Court in 2004, All Accused Let Off|publisher=}}</ref>
