{{use dmy dates|date=December 2013}} {{use list-defined references|date=December 2013}} {{Use British English|date=December 2013}} {{Infobox organization | name = European Association for Animal Production | former name = | image = | image_border = | size = <!-- default 200px --> | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = <!-- optional --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | map2 = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = | successor = | formation = 8 November 1949 | extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> | merger = | merged = | type = [[International nongovernmental organization|INGO]] | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = improvement of animal husbandry | headquarters = Via G. Tomassetti 3, A/1 | location = [[Rome]], Italy | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | region_served = | membership = | language = <!-- official languages --> | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | leader_title = President | leader_name = Matthias Gauly | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | key_people = | main_organ = council | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | affiliations = <!-- if any --> | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = {{url|http://www.eaap.org}} | remarks = }}
The '''European Federation for Animal Science''' or '''EAAP''' ({{lang-fr|'''Fédération Européenne de Zootechnie'''|italic=no}}; {{lang-de|'''Europäische Vereinigung für Tierproduktion'''|italic=no}}; {{lang-it|'''Federazione Europea di Zootecnia'''|italic=no}} [sic])<ref name=stat/> is an international [[non-governmental organisation]] which aims to improve the farming of [[domestic animals]]. Membership is open to scientists, animal breeders and administrators. The association was founded in Paris in 1949, and has its headquarters in [[Rome]], Italy.<ref name=john/> It was formerly known as the '''European Association for Animal Production'''.
Together with the [[British Society of Animal Science]] and the [[Institut national de la recherche agronomique]], it issues the [[academic journal]] [[Animal (journal)|''Animal'']], published by the [[Cambridge University Press]].
== History and purpose ==
The association was founded in Paris during the 5th [[International Congress on Animal Production]]. The inaugural meeting was held on 8 November 1949. Although the association was intended to be European in scope, the founding member countries were Austria, Belgium, Denmark, France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Morocco, the Netherlands, Spain, Switzerland and Tunisia,<ref name=john/> and thus included parts of both Africa and Asia.
The declared aim of the association is to:{{quote|"promote the improvement, organization and enlightened practice of animal production by scientific research, the application of science and co-operation between the national animal production organisations, scientists and practitioners of member countries".<ref name=john/>}}
